# No-op pre-commit hook.
#
# Intentionally empty. We deliberately do NOT run `npm test`, `npm run lint`,
# or `npm run build` here because:
#   - `npm test` has no corresponding package.json script (was the bug that
#     blocked every commit tonight until this was fixed)
#   - `npm run lint` on this codebase is noisy on legacy files and would
#     encourage `--no-verify` bypasses
#   - `npm run build` takes ~45s and is too slow for per-commit; it runs
#     pre-push instead (see .husky/pre-push)
#
# Build verification lives in .husky/pre-push. This hook is the right place
# for eventual fast checks (type-check a staged subset, secret-scan, etc.)
# if we want them later — but today, nothing is safer than something slow.
